             VISN1 Home Rumford Community Based Outpatient Clinic

   Photo of Rumford clinic entrance VA Rumford CBOC
                                                   191 Lincoln Avenue
                                                    Rumford, ME 04726
                                                  Phone: (207) 364-4098

                                                     Practice Hours:
                                                8:00am - 4:30pm, Mon-Fri
                                                  For after hours care,
                                               contact the Togus facility

                                      Directions

   The Rumford VA Clinic was opened into a fixed site location in November
   1998. The unique patient population has nearly tripled since that time
                      as the clinic continues to grow.

                              SERVICES PROVIDED
                 Primary Care and Preventive Health Services
                     Health Promotion/Disease Prevention
                         Medical Benefits Counseling
                                 Dermatology
                Laboratory Services supported by Togus Staff

                                KEY CONTACTS
                  Clinic Contact Point: Kenneth Burke, M.D.
                            Togus Contact Point:

     Richard P. Corbin, M.D., Primary Care Service Line Manager

     Penelope Graham, N.P., CBOC Firm Manager

                                 DIRECTIONS
                       (Distance from Togus: 60 miles)

     Rumford Clinic is located in the mountainous region of west central
    Maine. Follow Route 2 West from Bangor area and Route 108 from points
    East and South. When reaching Rumford, you will go through Mexico and
   back into Rumford as you cross the bridge. Continue straight up a steep
      hill; Route 2 turns left - don't. Go straight following signs to
             Hospital. Clinic is on left at 191 Lincoln Avenue.
